data.title: Los Angeles Clippers Roster
data.meta_description: Los Angeles Clippers scores, news, schedule, players, stats, rumors, depth charts and more on RealGM.com
data.text:
Blake Griffin was selected as the #1 pick in the First Round of the 2009 NBA Draft by the Los Angeles Clippers. Blake Griffin signed a multi-year contract with the Los Angeles Clippers on July 8, 2009.

DeAndre Jordan was selected as the #5 pick in the Second Round of the 2008 NBA Draft by the Los Angeles Clippers. DeAndre Jordan signed a multi-year contract with the Los Angeles Clippers on July 14, 2008. DeAndre Jordan re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on December 13, 2011.

Travis Leslie was selected as the #17 pick in the Second Round of the 2011 NBA Draft by the Los Angeles Clippers. Travis Leslie signed a multi-year contract with the Los Angeles Clippers on December 9, 2011.

Trey Thompkins was selected as the #7 pick in the Second Round of the 2011 NBA Draft by the Los Angeles Clippers. Trey Thompkins signed a multi-year contract with the Los Angeles Clippers on December 9, 2011.

Chris Paul was acquired in a trade by the Los Angeles Clippers from the New Orleans Pelicans on December 14, 2011.

Mo Williams was acquired in a trade by the Los Angeles Clippers from the Cleveland Cavaliers on February 24, 2011.

Nick Young was acquired in a trade by the Los Angeles Clippers from the Washington Wizards on March 15, 2012.

Chauncey Billups signed a contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on December 12, 2011.

Caron Butler signed a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on December 9, 2011.

Reggie Evans signed a contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on December 22, 2011.

Randy Foye signed a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on July 9, 2010.

Ryan Gomes signed a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on July 9, 2010.

Kenyon Martin signed a contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on February 3, 2012.

Bobby Simmons signed a contract with the Los Angeles Clippers on February 27, 2012. Bobby Simmons re-signed to a contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on March 9, 2012. Bobby Simmons re-signed to a contract as a free agent with the Los Angeles Clippers on March 24, 2012.
